; form-asm-exp-poly-band — the POLYNOMIAL EVALUATION ENGINE on the native asm lane: a degree-(n-1) Horner
; over a self-contained f64 pool, coefficients as a Form LIST (DATA), emits four-way as Form->asm BYTES, no rustc.
;
; The core-lift the whole exp lane was pointing at. fam-pool-fma (form-asm-exp-coef-pool) proved a SINGLE
; pooled fma (degree 1); fam-horner-list generalizes it to ANY degree in ONE engine — the coefficients are a
; list, the accumulator lives in d1 (x preserved in d0 across every fma), the FINAL fmadd targets d0 so no
; trailing fmov is needed. exp(r), sin, cos, gelu, silu are ALL Horner polynomials over pooled coefficients, so
; this one recipe is the transcendental evaluator each of them needs. Instantiated with the exp Taylor
; coefficients (1/720,1/120,1/24,1/6,1/2,1,1) it is fam-exp-poly, the exp(r) evaluator for r in [-ln2/2, ln2/2]
; (|error| < ~1.2e-7, bounded by r^7/7!) — the MISSING MIDDLE THIRD of a full native exp = 2^k * exp(r), between
; fam-exp-reduce (which yields r, #3935) and fam-pow2 (2^k, #3940).
;
; The layout math that generalizes (pinned against the M4 assembler oracle BEFORE authoring): for n coefficients
; the code is 2n words, the pool 8n bytes appended after ret. Each coefficient loads via a PC-relative literal
; (fa-ldr-d-lit) whose imm19 is the WORD distance to its pooled slot — 2n for the leading load and a CONSTANT
; 2n+1 for every tail load, because each tail step advances 2 words in code (ldr + fmadd) AND 2 words in the
; pool (a .quad is 2 words), so the distance is invariant. The pool bytes are computed by f64-bytes, so ANY
; value fills the pool — including 1/720 = 0x3f56c16c16c16c17, an irregular mantissa no hand pattern writes.
;
; The degree-6 exp image, otool -t of the M4 assembler oracle (13 code words + a 7-quad pool = 112 bytes):
;   0  ldr d1,+14  4 ldr d2,+15  8 fmadd d1,d1,d0,d2  c ldr d2,+15  10 fmadd d1,d1,d0,d2  14 ldr d2,+15
;   18 fmadd d1,d1,d0,d2  1c ldr d2,+15  20 fmadd d1,d1,d0,d2  24 ldr d2,+15  28 fmadd d1,d1,d0,d2
;   2c ldr d2,+15  30 fmadd d0,d1,d0,d2 (final -> d0)  34 ret  38.. .quad 1/720,1/120,1/24,1/6,1/2,1,1
;
; Verdict 15 when every claim lands:
;   1   the degree-6 exp program is 112 bytes (56 code + 56 pool)                          (len == 112)
;   2   the FULL 112-byte program byte-equals the M4 degree-6 assembler oracle             (fa-conviction == 1)
;   4   the layout math GENERALIZES — a degree-2 (n=3) Horner byte-equals its own M4 oracle (fa-conviction == 1)
;   8   coefficients are DATA — f64-bytes fills the pool with 1/720's irregular mantissa    (fa-conviction == 1)
;
; preludes: form-stdlib/format-arith.fk form-stdlib/f64-bytes.fk form-stdlib/form-asm.fk form-stdlib/form-asm-matvec.fk
(do
    (let prog (fam-exp-poly))
    (let oracle6 (list
        193 1 0 92    226 1 0 92    33 8 64 31    226 1 0 92    33 8 64 31
        226 1 0 92    33 8 64 31    226 1 0 92    33 8 64 31    226 1 0 92
        33 8 64 31    226 1 0 92    32 8 64 31    192 3 95 214
        23 108 193 22 108 193 86 63    17 17 17 17 17 17 129 63
        85 85 85 85 85 85 165 63       85 85 85 85 85 85 197 63
        0 0 0 0 0 0 224 63             0 0 0 0 0 0 240 63           0 0 0 0 0 0 240 63))
    (let oracle2 (list
        193 0 0 92    226 0 0 92    33 8 64 31    226 0 0 92    32 8 64 31    192 3 95 214
        0 0 0 0 0 0 224 63    0 0 0 0 0 0 240 63    0 0 0 0 0 0 240 63))
    (let c1 (if (eq (len prog) 112)                                                      1 0))
    (let c2 (if (eq (fa-conviction prog oracle6)                                    1)   2 0))
    (let c3 (if (eq (fa-conviction (fam-horner-list (list 0.5 1.0 1.0)) oracle2)    1)   4 0))
    (let c4 (if (eq (fa-conviction (fhl-pool (list (div 1.0 720.0)))
                                   (list 23 108 193 22 108 193 86 63))             1)   8 0))
    (add c1 (add c2 (add c3 c4))))
